text: Gatesville is a city in the U.S. state of Texas. It is the county seat of Coryell County. The population was 16,135 at the 2020 census. The city has five of the eight prisons and state jails for women operated by the Texas Department of Criminal Justice. One of the facilities, the Patrick O'Daniel Unit, has the state's death row for women. == References == Category:Cities in Texas Category:County seats in Texas
title: Gatesville, Texas
